TY  - JOUR
AU  - Demyanyk, Yuliya
AU  - Van Hemert, Otto
T1  - Understanding the Subprime Mortgage Crisis
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhp033
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 24
IS  - 6
SP  - 1848
EP  - 1880
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using loan-level data, we analyze the quality of subprime mortgage loans by adjusting their performance for differences in borrower characteristics, loan characteristics, and macroeconomic conditions. We find that the quality of loans deteriorated for six consecutive years before the crisis and that securitizers were, to some extent, aware of it. We provide evidence that the rise and fall of the subprime mortgage market follows a classic lending boom-bust scenario, in which unsustainable growth leads to the collapse of the market. Problems could have been detected long before the crisis, but they were masked by high house price appreciation between 2003 and 2005.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhp033
ER  - 



